The paper deals with data structures for maintaining embeddings of graphs on surfaces and computing generators of the fundamental group of the surface, which are topics in computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions a separator theorem for low-genus graphs, which falls under graph theory (cs.GT) and combinatorics (cs.DM). Additionally, the paper discusses finding tree-decompositions of low-genus low-diameter graphs, which is related to algorithms and complexity (cs.SI).
